<div class="hidden"><h1>crnrstn</h1>
		<p>When standing a web application up, the <a href="../../../documentation/classes/crnrstn/" target="_self">crnrstn</a> :: class object serves as the cornerstone block...securely joining the "wall" of the hosting environment to the "wall" of your application. When instantiating the class object, simply pass in the $_SERVER super global array, and crnrstn will absorb the characteristics of that particular hosting environment...then itself becoming the interface between the application and web server at critical and specified locations.<br />
<br />
Access to the <a href="../../../documentation/classes/crnrstn/" target="_self">crnrstn</a> :: class object is managed by the <a href="../../../documentation/classes/environmentals/" target="_self">environmentals</a> :: class object, and so upon the instantiation and configuring of crnrstn, the environmentals :: class object should be prepared immediately. Thenceforth, all references to content that would have otherwise been made available directly through the <a href="../../../documentation/classes/crnrstn/" target="_self">crnrstn</a> :: class object...will be accessed through the <a href="../../../documentation/classes/environmentals/" target="_self">environmentals</a> :: class object instead. See the documentation for the <a href="../../../documentation/classes/environmentals/" target="_self">environmentals</a> :: class for more information about how the application can access environmentally specific parameters relating to the hosting environment as it was configured through the <a href="../../../documentation/classes/crnrstn/" target="_self">crnrstn</a> :: class object.</p>
		<p>Version: 1.0.0</p><h2>Technical Specifications:</h2><p>Currently tested on an ubuntu 4.2 server running PHP Version 5.2.6 and Apache 2.2.11</p><p>It is recommended that you upgrade to the latest version of PHP to take advantage of the latest gains in security and processing efficiency.</p><h2>Methods:</h2><p><a href="http://crnrstn.jony5.com/documentation/classes/crnrstn/__construct/">__construct()</a><a href="http://crnrstn.jony5.com/documentation/classes/crnrstn/requireddetectionmatches/">requiredDetectionMatches()</a><a href="http://crnrstn.jony5.com/documentation/classes/crnrstn/addenvironment/">addEnvironment()</a><a href="http://crnrstn.jony5.com/classes/crdocumentation/nrstn/initlogging">initLogging()</a><a href="http://crnrstn.jony5.com/documentation/classes/crnrstn/initsessionencryption/">initSessionEncryption()</a><a href="http://crnrstn.jony5.com/documentation/classes/crnrstn/initcookieencryption/">initCookieEncryption()</a><a href="http://crnrstn.jony5.com/documentation/classes/crnrstn/grantexclusiveaccess/">grantExclusiveAccess()</a><a href="http://crnrstn.jony5.com/documentation/classes/crnrstn/denyaccess/">denyAccess()</a><a href="http://crnrstn.jony5.com/documentation/classes/crnrstn/adddatabase/">addDatabase()</a><a href="http://crnrstn.jony5.com/documentation/classes/crnrstn/defineenvresource/">defineEnvResource()</a></p><p>Last upated: 2017-04-11 02:27:10</p></div>